parties.raw_snippet:
between
Rogers Cable Communications Inc. (“Rogers”) and
EuroMedia Holdings Corp. (“Licensor”) offering EurocinemaSM Video-on-Demand service
made as of July 11 , 2006 (the “Effective Date”)
(the “Agreement")
parties.reasoning: The header of the agreement shows the contracting parties in the 'between' clause. These are the two named contracting entities: Rogers Cable Communications Inc. (referred to as “Rogers”) and EuroMedia Holdings Corp. (referred to as “Licensor”).

contract_type.reasoning: The agreement's title and the substantive obligations show that Licensor grants Rogers a non-exclusive license and right to distribute and exhibit entertainment programming on a Video-on-Demand basis. The core subject is licensing of content for distribution, so this is a license agreement.

notice_period.reasoning: There is no provision that requires advance notice to prevent an automatic renewal. Renewal occurs "At Rogers’ option" for a two-year term; the contract does not state an automatic renewal that a party can prevent by giving notice. Therefore no "notice to prevent automatic renewal" period exists in the contract.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: The term of this Agreement (the “Initial Term”) shall commence as of the Effective Date and, unless earlier terminated in accordance with this Agreement, shall terminate on June 30, 2010.
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 7 expressly states the Initial Term begins on the Effective Date and terminates on a specific calendar date (June 30, 2010). Because the contract provides a specific calendar expiration date, return it in ISO format.

renewal_term.raw_snippet: At Rogers’ option, this Agreement shall renew for a subsequent term of two (2) years on the terms and conditions herein (the “Renewal Term”).
renewal_term.reasoning: Section 7 grants Rogers the unilateral option to renew the agreement for a subsequent two-year term. This describes the renewal length and that renewal is at Rogers' option.
